Show HN: Grasshopper - Alternative tab manager for Firefox
text:
https://i.imgur.com/50hlPKi.jpg

Browser extension for tab management.

Shows a list of open tabs.

Tabs update in real time.

Powerful filter.

Pin tabs.

Close tabs.

Close multiple tabs.

Show pins or playing tabs.

Filter by title or url.

Re-open recently closed tabs.

Show tab titles or urls.

https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/grasshopper-urls/

Version 4.2 at this time of writing.

Ask HN: How to become a deep learning 'master' in 2022?
text:
Background: I know how to program (Python, C, Racket). I have done small projects and am confident on that front that if I understand the inner workings of something, then I can build that thing using code.

Now, I want to learn Deep Learning with emphasis on computer vision although it wouldn't hurt to learn other applications. But my focus is on core deep learning and computer vision.

I want to understand research papers, implement them from scratch (using something like PyTorch) and build new models to improve upon SOTA performance. By 'master' I mean all of the above.

How to go about that? Which courses, books, tutorials are the best to focus on? I know a bit of linear algebra and calculus and hope to pick up things as I go on.
